Day 11 â€“ Incident Response Basics (SOC Playbooks & IR Process)
ðŸ”¹ 1. What is Incident Response (IR)?

Incident Response = A structured approach to detect, contain, and recover from security incidents.

Goal: Minimize damage & restore operations quickly.

Handled by SOC Analysts + IR Team.

ðŸ”¹ 2. NIST Incident Response Lifecycle

Preparation â†’ Build tools, policies, playbooks.

Detection & Analysis â†’ Identify suspicious activity.

Containment â†’ Stop the attack from spreading.

Eradication â†’ Remove malicious files/backdoors.

Recovery â†’ Restore systems, monitor for reinfection.

Lessons Learned â†’ Document incident & improve defenses.

ðŸ”¹ 3. SOC Playbooks (Response Guides)

A playbook = Step-by-step guide for handling a specific incident.

Example Playbooks

Phishing Attack:

User reports suspicious email.

Check headers, URLs, attachments.

Block malicious domain.

Hunt similar emails in SIEM.

Brute Force Attack:

SIEM alert â†’ multiple failed logins.

Identify source IP.

Block IP at firewall.

Reset affected user passwords.

Malware Infection:

Endpoint alert triggered.

Isolate host from network.

Run malware scan + remove.

Collect artifacts for analysis.

