Task A: Create a Simple Playbook (Phishing)

Make a flowchart:

ðŸ“Œ Example steps:

User reports email â†’ SOC receives alert.

SOC Analyst checks headers & URLs.

If malicious â†’ block domain/IP.

Search SIEM for other recipients.

Escalate if widespread.


Task B: Simulate an Incident (Linux SSH Brute Force)

On attacker machine:

hydra -l root -P passwords.txt ssh://127.0.0.1


On defender machine: Check logs:

tail -f /var/log/auth.log


Response:

Block attacker IP:

sudo ufw deny from 192.168.1.10



Task C: Lessons Learned Report

Write a short Incident Report (1 page) with:

Incident type: Brute Force SSH

Detection: SIEM/Log alerts

Response: Blocked IP, reset password

Lessons: Enable 2FA, stricter password policy

